event: toxicology screening showed ethylene glycol traces
failed extubation on day 8 due to sputum retention
required two revisions due to bleeding
referred to tertiary hospital on day 16
thrombus in right internal jugular vein
chest X-ray showed infiltration of right lower lobe
metabolic alkalosis on admission to tertiary centre
immunoassay on free light chains on day 21
normal acid-base parameters reached on day 20
no need for renal replacement therapy
